8:
This is Palpebra. We come here a lot
when we need to do some shopping.
11:
These bargains aren't gonna last
forever! You there, miss! Why not
stop by and take a gander?
12:
Oh my gosh, look! Isn't that the
accessory featured in the Oculus?
It's sooo cute!
14:
Hey! I'm walkin' here! You tryin' to
piss me off or what?!
17:
What a... lively place. It's almost
making me dizzy.
20:
Ah... True. You came out here to
relax, so maybe Palpebra wasn't the
best place to go. Should we head
somewhere else?
24:
No, it's fine. I'm the one who wanted
to see this for myself.
28:
But why? There are plenty of towns
like this in the Kingdom of Sand.
Especially towards the capitol.
37:
Everyone here feels so... positive.
There's strength in their eyes.
40:
I think I get it. Anyone living in a town
made up of merchants and
adventurers is bound to have a glint
in their eyes.
44:
Yeah, but that glint sometimes
means trouble...
47:
Hey, you there! Feeling hungry? 
How about some donuts?
50: Yeah, why not? We'll take five!
59: Ah, do you not like sweets?
70:
Yeah... Can't really tell what you're
thinking with just "mm"... How about
using words?
77:
I'll take another, but this time, give
me that flavor.
81: Jeez, you really love this stuff, huh?
85:
Of course. Finding something this
sweet is rare in my world.
88:
I can't believe you can just buy it off
the street here...
95:
Well... I wouldn't say that prosperity
is evenly distributed though...
103:
Stop, thief! Somebody, stop that
man!
109:
I'll give chase while you circle
around! That way we can corner
him!
113:
Come on! You're supposed to be on
vacation!
121: Shut up and get outta my face!
129:
...No matter where we go or how
much we prosper, people never
change.
136: No... I'm even more determined now.
139:
This place was created by people
just like me...
141:
That means someday my world can
thrive like this as well.
145:
You know, fifty years ago, none of
this existed.
149:
I see... That doesn't mean my home
will turn out the same way, but...
152: A man can dream, I guess.
155:
...Looks like I've got a lot of work
ahead of me.
167:
There are a few people in Starview
that are studying Palpebra's rise to
success too.
171:
Interesting... Would it be possible to
meet them?
175:
And Nimbus... I'd like to ask about
your late friend as well.
178:
...This ain't the place for that kinda
story.
180:
But sure, why not? We can reminisce
over drinks at the pub.
191:
Perhaps you could get something
sweet instead.
195: Heh... Now that's more like it.
